4.1 By clicking “Apply”, submitting an Application, joining a Team, attending any Competition event (including online sessions, workshops or the Residency), or otherwise taking part in the Competition, you agree to be bound by these Terms, the Competition rules on the Competition Website, and any additional instructions that Roop Stone communicates to Participants.

4.2 If you are participating on behalf of a Team, you confirm that you are authorised to accept these Terms on behalf of all Team members and that all Team members agree to be bound by them.

5. APPLICATION & SELECTION
5.1 Application Process.
Applications must be submitted through the online form or method specified on the Competition Website, and must include all required information and materials (including portfolios, CVs, concept notes or design samples) by the deadline stated on the Competition Website.

5.2 Accuracy.
You warrant that all information provided in your Application is true, accurate, complete and not misleading. You must promptly notify Roop Stone of any changes to such information.

5.3 Number of Entries.
Roop Stone may limit the number of Applications per person or Team and may reject multiple or duplicate Applications at its discretion.

5.4 Screening & Shortlisting.
Roop Stone will evaluate Applications using criteria such as design quality, originality, feasibility, alignment with the Competition brief, and potential for commercialization, as described on the Competition Website. Roop Stone may conduct interviews, online challenges or additional rounds of screening.

5.5 Selection Decisions.
All decisions of Roop Stone and its jury regarding eligibility, shortlisting, selection for the Residency, and selection of Winning Teams are final and binding, and no correspondence, appeal or challenge will be entertained.

5.6 Roop Stone may, at any time and for any reason, refuse any Application or remove any Participant or Team from consideration if, in its opinion, they do not comply with these Terms or the spirit of the Competition.

6. TEAMS
6.1 Participants may apply individually and/or as Teams, as specified on the Competition Website. Roop Stone may assist in forming Teams by matching individuals with complementary skills, but final Team composition remains subject to Roop Stone’s approval.

6.2 Each Team must designate one Team Leader who will be the primary point of contact with Roop Stone and who is authorised to receive communications, sign acknowledgements and make decisions on behalf of the Team. However, each Team member remains individually bound by these Terms.

6.3 Roop Stone will not be responsible for any internal arrangements, disputes, revenue‑sharing, or ownership issues among Team members. Teams are solely responsible for agreeing among themselves how any rights, responsibilities or benefits are shared.

6.4 Roop Stone may, in its sole discretion, permit changes in Team composition (e.g., addition or replacement of members) subject to written approval and any conditions it prescribes.

7. COMPETITION STRUCTURE & TIMELINE
7.1 The Competition is broadly structured into several phases, as further detailed on the Competition Website. These may include:

a. Phase I – Open Call / Virtual Immersion: online community, introductory workshops, and preliminary design or concept submissions;
b. Phase II – Pitch / Gateway: refinement of concepts, business and marketing plans, and presentation to Roop Stone for shortlisting;
c. Phase III – Residency (Rajasthan): an in‑person design and product‑development sprint at Roop Stone’s facilities; and
d. Phase IV – Launch: potential market launch and commercialization of selected products.

7.2 Roop Stone may modify, postpone, shorten, suspend or cancel any phase of the Competition; change dates, venues, formats (online vs in‑person) or deliverables; or adjust the number of Participants/Teams at each stage, at any time, with or without notice, for any reason including operational or public‑health reasons.

7.3 Participation in the Residency and subsequent phases is subject to your continued compliance with these Terms, any additional participation agreements (including health & safety and facility‑use rules), and any other documents Roop Stone may require you to sign.

